{
  "stem": "27390.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they-- after about two weeks, they closed-- they fenced around the-- the-- the area of the ghetto, with barbed wire and with watchtowers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And every 50 yards was a guard, with a machine gun, with a-- it was such a hut, where they stood there, guard post.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this was us from the outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from inside, they had the Jewish police patrolling, making sure that nobody goes near the-- the fence.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whoever came near the fence, if he-- if he was getting to near, he was shot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so people did-- avoided to go near the fence unless somebody wanted to commit suicide.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some people, they committed-- they wanted to commit suicide, so they walked near the fence, and they got shot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's how they closed off the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, they gave an order that everybody should-- they opened a bank.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Couldn't understand what they were opening a bank for.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we realized the bank was everybody should bring in their valuables, their currency, their foreign currency.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they exchanged it for ghetto money, money that was printed for the ghetto, only, which was worthless outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in the ghetto, you could buy the rations with it, whatever they were.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they started introducing rations.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It took some time till they organized.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody had a ration book.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you got some food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But Rumkowski, after collecting all the money, and they handed it over to the Germans, he had to do what he's told.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He took orders from the Germans, and he carried them out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a very faithful-- To this day, nobody understands why he was so-- he did it with such enthusiasm.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
